Package it.unipr.sowide.actodes.executor.passive

Provides classes defining the executor actors that drive the execution of passive actors.
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Selector
    The Selector interface defines a selector for moving the actors in the persistent storage based on both the number of its last idle cycles and the number of scheduled actors.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CycleProcessing
    The CycleProcessing defines a logging object constraint that allows to accept only all the logging of the processing of cycle messages coming from the actor executor.
    CycleScheduler
    The CycleScheduler class uses the "cooperative scheduling" mechanism for executing CycleActor actors.
    DefaultSelector
    The DefaultSelector class defines the default implementation of a selector for actors to move in the persistent storage.
    OldScheduler
    The OldScheduler class uses the "cooperative scheduling" mechanism for executing OldActor actors.
    OneScheduler
    The OneScheduler class uses the "cooperative scheduling" mechanism for executing OneActor actors.
    PersistentScheduler
    The PersistentScheduler class uses the "cooperative scheduling" mechanism for executing SavableActor actors.
    Scheduler<A extends PassiveActor>
    The Scheduler class provides a partial implementation of a behavior of the executor actor used for creating and executing passive actors.
    SharedScheduler
    The SharedScheduler class uses the "cooperative scheduling" mechanism for executing SharedActor actors.
    TemporaryScheduler
    The TemporaryScheduler class uses the "cooperative scheduling" mechanism for executing SavableActor actors.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Scheduler.Cycle
    The Cycle enumeration defines an event that an executor actor for passive actors may use for informing about the end of an execution cycle of the actors of the actor space.
